From: claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-06-09
Subject: [PATCH] go-builder: pin to 1.26.4-alpine to close Go stdlib CVEs

Closes GO-2026-4918, GO-2026-4971, GO-2026-4980, GO-2026-4982,
GO-2026-5037, GO-2026-5039 — all Go stdlib vulns flagged by
govulncheck against homechef-api at Go 1.26.2.

The Dockerfile already used `golang:1.26-alpine` (floating major.minor
tag), so the weekly rebuild would have picked these up automatically
on the next Saturday run. Pinning to `1.26.4-alpine` makes the bump
deliberate + immediate so downstream services can drop their stopgap
overrides.

Apply with:
  cd <path-to>/base-docker-images
  git checkout -b bump/go-1.26.4
  patch -p1 < /path/to/base-image-go-1.26.4.patch
  git commit -am "go-builder: pin to 1.26.4-alpine (Go stdlib CVE fixes)"
  git push origin bump/go-1.26.4
  # then open PR; once merged, weekly-rebuild.yml or a manual
  # workflow_dispatch publishes the new :latest / :weekly tags.

After base-go-builder:latest ships Go 1.26.4, revert the stopgap in
Home-Chef-App/apps/api/Dockerfile:
  FROM golang:1.26.4-alpine AS builder   ->
  FROM ghcr.io/tesserix/base-go-builder:latest AS builder
(and drop the apk add line — base image already has those).

---
 images/go-builder/Dockerfile | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/images/go-builder/Dockerfile b/images/go-builder/Dockerfile
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/images/go-builder/Dockerfile
+++ b/images/go-builder/Dockerfile
@@ -7,7 +7,7 @@
 #
 # Non-root user is baked at 10001 so consumers can `USER 10001:10001` in
 # their own Dockerfile without adding duplicate adduser commands.
-FROM golang:1.26-alpine
+FROM golang:1.26.4-alpine

 # Force each weekly rebuild to pull the freshest apk index — without
 # --purge, the layer cache can silently hold month-old package sets.
